===Cardinal Number===
'''kahdeksan'''

#[[eight]]

===Etymology===
A compound of kah- and deksan. The former comes from [[kaksi]], while the latter is from the same common Indo-European root ''*dek-'' as e.g. Latin [[decem]] and Hungarian [[tíz]]. So the compound originally meant two (from) ten.

